          <title>The US is killing someone by firing squad for the 1st time in 15 years. Here's a look at the history</title>
          <description><![CDATA[It was a punishment for mutiny in colonial times, a way to discourage desertion during the Civil War and a dose of frontier justice in the Old West. In modern times, some consider it a more humane alternative to lethal injection. The firing squad has a long and thorny history in the U.S.]]></description>
